Here&#39;s a simple recursive technique. It is similar to Nina&#39;s but it preserves arrays, if present in the structure.

1. If the input, `t`, is an array, create a new array by traversing each array value, `v`, with the traversing function, `f`
2. (inductive) Otherwise `t` is _not_ an array. If `t` is an object, create a new object from key value pairs, `[ k, v ]`, by traversing each value, `v`, with the traversing function, `f`
3. (inductive) Otherwise `t` is _not_ an array and `t` is _not_ an object. This means `t` is either a primitive value, such as string, number, or `null`

