**FIRST SOLUTION**

here is the [stackBlitz Demo](https://mat-tree-with-dragging-2-e2rgyu.stackblitz.io)

here is the [stackBlitz editable link](https://stackblitz.com/edit/mat-tree-with-dragging-2-e2rgyu?file=app/tree-flat-overview-example.html)

I&#39;ve made a recursive call on every visible node reffering to the node index using `treeControl.dataNodes.indexOf(node)`

here is the recursive function:

      recNode(arr:any[], data:any[], index:number, maxIndex:number):any[]{
        if (arr === undefined)
          arr = [];
        for (let i = 0; i &lt; data.length; i++){
              index++
              if (index === maxIndex)
                return ([true, index, arr]);
              if (data[i].children.length){
                let res = this.recNode(arr, data[i].children, index, maxIndex)
                index = res[1];
                if (res[0] === true)
                {
                  arr.splice(0, 0, (i !== (data.length - 1)))         
                  return ([true, index, arr]);
                }
            }
        }
        return ([false, index, arr]);
      }

this returns an array of `true` `false` values for your `[ngClass]`

